cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper proposes an ensemble of deep learned features for melanoma classification, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) as feature extractors and support vector machines (SVMs) for classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of different CNN architectures and learning parameter sets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of SVMs for classification indicates that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of internal layers of CNNs as descriptors, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with image classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
